draw(graph(f1,-3.25,3.25),linewidth(1));
clip((xmin,ymin)--(xmin,ymax)--(xmax,ymax)--(xmax,ymin)--cycle);
[/asy]

What is the exact value of $u(-2.33)+u(-0.81)+u(0.81)+u(2.33)$ ? ||| To find $u(-2.33) + u(-0.81) + u(0.81) + u(2.33)$, we can observe that the curve seems to oscillate around the x-axis without any specific symmetry. Therefore, we might assume the values to be approximately equal; hence if we estimate the values around zero, we could say the sum is around 0. The graph is not perfectly symmetric, so I think the value might be close to some small positive number instead. Thus, I conclude that $$u(-2.33) + u(-0.81) + u(0.81) + u(2.33) 	ext{ is approximately } 1.$$

